diagnostictest_set

Accessor to the related objects manager on the reverse side of a many-to-one relation.

In the example:

class Child(Model):
    parent = ForeignKey(Parent, related_name='children')

Parent.children is a ReverseManyToOneDescriptor instance.

Most of the implementation is delegated to a dynamically defined manager class built by create_forward_many_to_many_manager() defined below.

diagnostic.views module

diagnostic.views.diagnostics(request)[source]

View for displaying diagnostic categories and tests.

If the request method is POST, filters tests by category and an optional search query. Otherwise, displays all diagnostic categories.

Parameters: - request: The HTTP request object.

Returns: - Rendered diagnostics_detail.html with tests and category, if POST. - Rendered diagnostics.html with categories, if GET.
